---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';

const publishDate = new Date("2025-04-02");
const formattedDate = publishDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
  year: 'numeric', 
  month: 'long', 
  day: 'numeric' 
});
---

<Layout 
  title="Video Game Arcades: A Lost Social Experience"
  description="Before online gaming, arcades were social hubs where gamers gathered to compete and connect. We explore this uniquely physical gaming culture that has largely disappeared from our digital world."
>
  <Hero 
    title="Video Game Arcades: A Lost Social Experience"
    subtitle={`Published on ${formattedDate} by Marcus Chen`}
    image="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3017630/pexels-photo-3017630.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2"
    height="medium"
  />
  
  <article class="py-16 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert lg:prose-lg mx-auto">
          <p class="lead">
            In the 1980s and early 1990s, video game arcades were more than just places to play games – they were vibrant social spaces where friendships were forged, rivalries were born, and gaming culture flourished.
          </p>

          <h2>The Golden Age of Arcades</h2>
          <p>
            During their peak in the 1980s, arcades were everywhere: shopping malls, movie theaters, convenience stores, and standalone locations. These neon-lit spaces were filled with the sounds of electronic beeps, the clinking of quarters, and the excited chatter of players.
          </p>

          <figure class="my-8">
            <img 
              src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3945683/pexels-photo-3945683.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
              alt="Retro arcade machines" 
              class="rounded-lg shadow-lg"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-dark-500 dark:text-dark-400 mt-2">
              Classic arcade machines that defined an era of gaming
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

          <h2>A Social Hub</h2>
          <p>
            Unlike today's online gaming, arcade gaming was inherently social. Players had to be physically present, sharing the same space, watching each other play, and waiting their turn. This created a unique atmosphere of camaraderie and competition.
          </p>

          <h2>The Rise of Home Gaming</h2>
          <p>
            The decline of arcades began with the increasing sophistication of home gaming consoles. As systems like the Nintendo Entertainment System and Sega Genesis brought arcade-quality gaming into people's homes, the need for arcades diminished.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            "Arcades weren't just about the games – they were about the community, the competition, and the shared experience of discovering new worlds together."
          </blockquote>

          <h2>Legacy and Modern Revival</h2>
          <p>
            While traditional arcades have largely disappeared, their influence lives on. Modern "barcades" combine classic arcade games with adult beverages, and esports venues carry on the tradition of social gaming spaces.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center my-12 p-6 bg-dark-50 dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Visit Our Gaming Exhibition</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Experience classic arcade games and learn about the evolution of gaming culture in our interactive exhibition.
              </p>
              <a 
                href="/exhibitions/gaming-evolution" 
                class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
              >
                Learn more about the exhibition
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4 ml-1">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5 21 12m0 0-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
            <img 
              src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3945683/pexels-photo-3945683.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
              alt="Retro gaming setup" 
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 rounded-lg shadow-md"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Author Bio -->
        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark-200 dark:border-dark-700">
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <img 
              src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2379004/pexels-photo-2379004.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
              alt="Marcus Chen" 
              class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full object-cover mr-4"
            />
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-dark-900 dark:text-white">Marcus Chen</h3>
              <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300">
                Gaming Historian and Curator
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Share and Navigation -->
        <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap justify-between items-center pt-8 border-t border-dark-200 dark:border-dark-700">
          <div class="flex space-x-4">
            <button class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 hover:text-primary-600 dark:hover:text-primary-400">
              Share on Twitter
            </button>
            <button class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 hover:text-primary-600 dark:hover:text-primary-400">
              Share on Facebook
            </button>
          </div>
          <a 
            href="/blog" 
            class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
          >
            Back to Blog
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dark-50 dark:bg-dark-800/50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-dark-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-12">
        Related Articles
      </h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/442576/pexels-photo-442576.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="Gaming consoles" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The Evolution of Gaming Consoles
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              From the Atari 2600 to modern gaming systems: a journey through time.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/evolution-gaming-consoles" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2263818/pexels-photo-2263818.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="Retro controllers" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The Art of Game Design
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              How video game design has evolved from pixels to photorealism.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/art-game-design" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2885014/pexels-photo-2885014.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="Gaming community" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The Rise of Esports
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              How competitive gaming became a global phenomenon.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/rise-of-esports" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  
  .prose img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: inherit;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  
  .prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 4px solid theme('colors.primary.600');
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  .dark .prose blockquote {
    border-left-color: theme('colors.primary.400');
  }
</style>